                        <h2>About Me</h2>
                        <p>
                            I'm a software engineer and teacher from Portugal, working in client-server, desktop and mobile
                            application development, being proficient with C, Java, JavaScript, C# and PHP programming
                            languages, along with HTML5 and CSS.
                        </p>
                        
                        <h2>Experience</h2>
                        <p>
                            I've worked on projects ranging from simple WEB applications in PHP, to full-blown enterprise
                            projects mixing WEB and desktop technologies, integrating complex systems, developing mobile
                            applications and their supporting server software.
                        </p>
                        
                        <h2>Open Source</h2>
                        <p>
                            Along with non-free (the typical "commercial") projects, I also develop or help develop several
                            free software projects. Some of those projects can be seen in 
                            <a href="https://bitbucket.org/Knitter/workspace/repositories/" target="_blank">BitBucket</a>,
                            <a href="https://github.com/Knitter" target="_blank">GitHub</a>, or
                            <a href="https://notabug.org/Knitter" target="_blank">NotABug</a>.
